Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.80,0:00:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I promised Akil I’d go out \Nin service with him after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.22,0:00:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Hey, we’re just waiting in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.35,0:00:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And I kept my word, 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.52,0:00:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‎but my head just wasn’t in it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.66,0:00:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Akil could tell, so he tried \Nto see if everything was OK. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.71,0:01:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Honestly, at the time, 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I would have rather been playing \Nvideo games, 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.88,0:01:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‎but I couldn’t tell him that. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.72,0:01:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I mean, \Nhe’s a pioneer, a ministerial servant. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.72,0:01:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‎He wouldn’t understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.62,0:01:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Later that week, 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.62,0:01:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Akil invited me \Nto go mountain biking with some friends. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.25,0:01:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‎It was actually really fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.63,0:01:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,‎. . . and your croissant.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.01,0:01:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Great, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.68,0:01:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Please let me know \Nif there’s anything else, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.39,0:01:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎All right. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.47,0:01:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So, Danny, \Nyou’re obviously good at biking. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‎What else do you like to do for fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‎OK, so I have this game and it’s called . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.48,0:02:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Soon I was showing him my video games. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.78,0:02:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And surprisingly, \Nhe liked video games too. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.32,0:02:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But he said he chose to be selective. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.75,0:02:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎He began to describe \Nthe gladiators in ancient Rome. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.38,0:02:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,‎People would come from all over 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.01,0:02:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‎to watch them fight to the death. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And while the spectators \Nweren’t in any physical danger, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.73,0:02:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the real danger came over time. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.07,0:02:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Repeatedly watching \Nthe bloodshed and the killing, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:03:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‎it was dulling their senses, \Nand they wanted more of it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‎This was a big test \Nfor the Christians who lived back then. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Akil helped me to reason on the scripture
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,‎at Romans 12:9: 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.64,0:03:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“Abhor what is wicked; \Ncling to what is good.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So, Danny,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.40,0:03:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the games may have changed over time, 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.69,0:03:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎but the violence is still the same. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I like video games, 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.24,0:03:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‎but I avoid the ones \Nthat promote what Jehovah hates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Jehovah’s people can still have fun. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.76,0:04:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And, yeah, \Nwe can even play video games. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.10,0:04:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I just want to make wise choices. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.19,0:04:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I want to show Jehovah \Nthat I hate wickedness 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and make his heart glad.
